ode","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Allows to select the balance between result accuracy (precision) and missed barcodes (recall) for linear barcodes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Some barcode types are naturally prone to false positives (e.g. MSI Plessey).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For those barcode types false positives can be drastically reduced (precision can be increased) by requiring that multiple scan-lines in the input scan to the same result.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, this stronger condition can lead to missed barcodes (lower recall).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Confirmation is avoided for barcode types, which are by design resistant to false positives, (e.g. Code128) to maximize recall.","type":"text"}]},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode/minimal":{"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkonedconfirmationmode\/minimal","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode.minimal","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Minimal confirmation is performed. Compared to no confirmation, it provides a substantial decrease in false positives (increased precision), at the cost of a minimal decrease in recall."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKOneDConfirmationModeMinimal","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKOneDConfirmationMode\/minimal","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"minimal","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK":{"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Version: 8.0.4","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK","type":"topic","role":"collection","title":"ScanbotSDK"}},"variantOverrides":[{"patch":[{"path":"\/identifier\/interfaceLa